                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.5216/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fisher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-08T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 8, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. With reference to my despatch 827, October 15th,<note n="90"
                        xml:id="d501fn90">Not printed.</note> Diego Buigas, who resigned as Spanish
                    Chargé d’Affaires ad interim here to support the revolution, informs me that the
                    Salvadoran Government this morning recognized the Burgos Government and extended
                    recognition to him as Chargé.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fisher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
